Federal Reserve policy makers will
hold four two-day meetings and four one-day meetings in 2012,
the same as planned for this year, the central bank said in a
statement in  Washington  today.  Next yearâ€™s meetings of the  Federal Open Market Committee 
will take place Jan. 24-25; March 13; April 24-25; June 19-20;
July 31; Sept. 12; Oct. 23-24; and Dec. 11. The first session of
2013 will occur Jan. 29-30, the tentative meeting schedule
